---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: Security+ SY0-701 Practice Test
description: Start a randomized CompTIA Security+ SY0-701 practice test and review the reasoning behind each answer.
permalink: /security-plus/sy0-701/practice-test/
---
{% set quiz = quizCatalog.currentQuiz %}
<header class="page-header">
  <div class="page-shell">
    <nav class="breadcrumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <ol>
        <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
        <li><a href="/security-plus/">Security+</a></li>
        <li><a href="/security-plus/practice-test/">Practice tests</a></li>
        <li aria-current="page">SY0-701</li>
      </ol>
    </nav>
    <p class="eyebrow">{{ quiz.test.testId }} question bank</p>
    <h1>Security+ SY0-701 practice test</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      This page is the permanent home for the SY0-701 quiz application.
    </p>
  </div>
</header>

<section class="section">
  <div class="page-shell">
    <div class="callout">
      <strong>Phase 2 question-data pipeline is ready.</strong>
      <p>
        Each production build now validates the active CSV, runs conversion tests, and creates browser-ready JSON from approved questions only. The interactive quiz interface will be connected in Phase 3.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card-grid" aria-label="Current quiz data status">
      <article class="card">
        <p class="card__meta">Approved questions</p>
        <h2>{{ quiz.availableQuestionCount }}</h2>
        <p>Loaded from the active SEC-701 question file without draft or retired records.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <p class="card__meta">Available test length</p>
        <h2>{{ quiz.defaultQuestionCount }}</h2>
        <p>The 30-question default will activate automatically when the approved bank is large enough.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <p class="card__meta">Runtime data version</p>
        <h2>Versioned</h2>
        <p>A content hash identifies the exact public question data used by each build.</p>
      </article>
    </div>

    <ul class="status-list" aria-label="Question data protections">
      <li><span class="status-list__icon" aria-hidden="true">✓</span><span>Only approved rows from questions.csv are published</span></li>
      <li><span class="status-list__icon" aria-hidden="true">✓</span><span>Answer identities remain stable after display-order shuffling</span></li>
      <li><span class="status-list__icon" aria-hidden="true">✓</span><span>Internal review notes and source-management fields are excluded</span></li>
      <li><span class="status-list__icon" aria-hidden="true">✓</span><span>Generated quiz JSON is excluded from search indexing</span></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>
